Political Capital: the Hungarian Guard increased the country&#39;s risk
According to the Risk Analyzing Division of Political Capital, the activities of the Hungarian Guard, founded in August of this year with the support of the Jobbik Hungary Movement, increased the political risk of Hungary and the region in several aspects.
In the company&#39;s &quot;risk warning&quot;, it was written that the greatest political risk in connection with the activities of the Hungarian Guard is that &quot;with the worsening of the ethnic tension that already exists between the Gypsy and non-Gypsy population in Hungary, violent ethnic clashes may even develop in the short term&quot;.
The main reason for this is that the Hungarian Guard&#39;s political strategy is probably aimed at provoking such an act, the research institute added.
As they wrote, all of this can be traced back to one of the main omissions of Hungarian political actors: &quot;the public discussion of the Roma issue was left to representatives of radical and extreme political groups, who could build a political strategy on the Gypsy-Hungarian conflict&quot;.
This deepens the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens the extremists, and increases the likelihood of violent conflicts - they believe.
In addition, according to the research institute, the activities of the Hungarian Guard, as a result of the great domestic and international media attention, &quot;significantly worsened the image of Hungary abroad, especially in terms of faith in the country&#39;s stability and democratic development&quot;.
They remind you: as part of the reorganization of radical and far-right groups in Hungary, which gained more and more publicity and momentum starting from the fall of 2006, several organizations calling themselves &quot;national self-defense&quot; associations were founded in Hungary in the summer of 2007.
&quot;The common feature of these gatherings is that they define themselves as civil organizations, while openly promoting the preparation of their members - even armed - for defense (disaster prevention, national defense, law enforcement) tasks, in addition citing the incompetence of the police, the army, that is, the state,&quot; they added.
It was noted: all this is done in accordance with the method which, based on society&#39;s opposition to politics and parties, tries to put various political aspirations in a civil guise.
