That&#39;s how the six-member choir came together - i.e. Sena, Edina Kutzora, Judie Jay, Bori Péterfy, Enikő Hodosi [Neo], Juci Németh - which we later named Underground Divas.
hvg.hu: Did you plan the song just like that or did the girls perform it?
Zs.B.: The track has existed in an instrumental version for a long time, and when the material for the album was assembled, we thought that this track needed something more.
The chord progression attracted him to add a vocal part to it.
That same night, I sang the melody to him, which the girls later learned.
It all came almost at first and frighteningly spontaneously.
I remember it was very electrifying at the time, but of course you needed the Divas.
It wouldn&#39;t have worked as powerfully with my voice.
hvg.hu: Both on the album and in the concert, it seemed that the girls were in the background.
There are no solos (except for Judy Jay&#39;s short solo), they don&#39;t have their own parts, they sing completely together and are not louder than the music, so the music doesn&#39;t just accompany their singing.
They also stood at the back of the stage.
Is this intentional?
Zs.B.: The fact that they were behind was purely due to technical problems.
On the other hand, it is conscious that we did not want to share solo roles.
The track is also about this, to forget our ego a little, who came from where, where we are going, just let those certain wings, the wings of love, lift us up.
I wanted others to feel the euphoric state we felt when the song was born.
hvg.hu: Which one did you work with the most?
Zs.B.: In the musical creative process, there were actually more difficult pieces with none of them, but rather with the mixing.
For example, Dorian Gray&#39;s Dilemma, in which I play on a competition piano, or Rock&#39;n&#39;Roll Goes To The Girls, where the groove didn&#39;t want to work for a long time, and then slowly everything fell into place, like a puzzle game.
hvg.hu: Which is your favorite track from the new album?
Zs.B.: This is constantly changing with concerts and the fact that I have already &quot;released&quot; the record.
