You can put your signature on the wall of Bodeguita in Havana.
In the bar of the expensive Nacional Hotel, they will mix you a cocktail of your choice.
And the cult cars of the 1950s still drive in Havana today, as the once-exported zhigulis and fiats have long since rotted in this salty and humid air.
