Other places are getting nicer too, like Trinidad.
Considering that tourism provides the much-needed money, its development was given the green light.
In the last fifteen years, new hotels have been built not only in Havana, but also in Varader, on the coast of the province of Holguín, and on islands such as Cayo Coco, Cayo Guillermo and others.
Cuba offers another unique delicacy in the world, which is primarily appreciated by train lovers.
From their extensive plantations, sugar cane was transported to the sugar mills by steam and motor trains.
Their motor park has not been renovated for decades, so you can see working machines, whose contemporaries can only be seen elsewhere in museums.
