What kind of insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which provides security for the car owner against various damage events, brings significant expenses and depends on several factors, such as age, gender, date of obtaining the driver&#39;s license, marital status, type of car to be insured and the nature of its use.
Buying a car is only the first step.
Moreover, choosing the right insurance is often more difficult than deciding what kind of car we want.
First, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured.
This agreement takes the form of an insurance contract, which states that the insurance company undertakes to pay compensation in the event of a damage event in exchange for a fixed insurance premium.
The insurance premium is practically the amount paid for the insurance, which is determined by taking into account various factors, such as age, gender, date of obtaining the driver&#39;s license, marital status, type of car to be insured, its use, and others.
Insurance companies determine the insurance premium based on statistics, i.e. those with a higher accident risk pay a higher amount.
That&#39;s why people over 25 or women pay less, because according to statistics, they are less of a risk because they are more careful.
Similarly, based on the findings, insurance companies have concluded that married people also cause fewer accidents than single people.
The frequency is decisive for the type of use of the car.
With more frequent use, the possibility of an accident increases.
Many factors are taken into account by insurance companies when determining the insurance premium.
Therefore, the owner must look carefully in order to choose the most suitable form of insurance for his profile.
In the following, we present the most important factors when choosing, so that the needs of the insured can be best adapted to and an acceptable price can be established.
When concluding an insurance contract, those under the age of 25 have to take into account a number of disadvantages, such as a lack of driving experience and a recent driver&#39;s license.
Although it is most ideal if we are insured against all dangers, there are also more economical solutions.
More cautious drivers can take out complete insurance with a deductible, thus they will be insured against all dangers, and the price will be affordable.
In this type of contract, the insured pays part of the damage.
&quot;The amount of the deductible that the insured has to pay depends on the insurance premium; the higher the premium, the lower the deductible,&quot; says Luis Noguera, Spain manager of Internet insurance broker First Europa.
Another option is extended liability insurance for third parties, where the customer insures himself against damage caused to others, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, you will be insured against theft, fire damage and loss of the car.
A good advice.
If you are not yet 25 years old, be careful and avoid accidents as much as possible, because this affects the bonus and thus you can reduce the amounts to be paid in the future.
Discounts compared to the basic tariff of the insurance company are called bonuses.
The penalty charged compared to the basic tariff is called malus.
&quot;The amount of bonus and penalty depends on the insurance company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year, it can afford to increase the bonus rate,&quot; explains Noguera.
Once the age limit of 25 has been crossed, it is easier for owners to take out adequate insurance, as the risk of accidents decreases thanks to the experience gained over the years.
In that case, we advise you to take out comprehensive insurance with a deductible.
&quot;In general, young people are not yet able to properly apply their experience during an accident, not even when driving,&quot; says the director of the European insurance company in Spain, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of driving, when the drivers have already passed the on the fear of beginners.
If the insured is already married but does not yet have children, it is best to take out complete insurance, of course if your financial means allow it.
Insurance companies consider married couples with children to be the least risky customers, so the premium to be paid is lower in their case.
In this case, it is best to have complete insurance with a deductible (this can reach 300 euros), or if they have a higher bonus, they can extend the insurance to include damage caused to others from the third year of the vehicle.
&quot;They drive more calmly, but at the same time they have more purchasing power and can afford a higher deductible,&quot; confirms Luis Noguera.
In the case of pensioners, we recommend complete insurance with a deductible (which is around 150 euros), or in the case of a higher bonus, it can also be extended to liability insurance.
Car insurance is very important, not only because it protects the owner in the event of damage, but also because it is a big expense, so it is essential to choose the appropriate form of insurance.
