He said if the increased confusion persists, it could raise the possibility of further tightening of credit conditions for households and businesses.
The statements were interpreted by investors to mean that the Fed is ready to inject fresh capital into the US markets or even to further cut interest rates in order to stabilize credit conditions.
The statements also had a calming effect on Wall Street, which has recently been hit by several bad news concerning the American economy. Such was the case, for example, with the negative record of the number of US home sales.
The side effect of the financial unrest was also reinforced by the announcement of the Bear Stearns investment bank that it is laying off 650 workers, or 4 percent of its global workforce, as part of cost reductions in order to offset the losses achieved in the US secondary mortgage sector.
A total of 20 jobs at the London headquarters, which employs 1,500 workers, will be affected by the above measure.
