In this way, higher education institutions cooperate closely with neighboring countries, if only because of tradition.
The University of Saarbrücken was founded by the French in 1948.
To this day, students here can complete their studies with a double or even triple degree.
Accordingly, the proportion of foreign students is high at 15.6 percent.
