&quot;We initiated a number of reforms in primary schools following the first Pisa study,&quot; said a spokesperson for the Ministry of Education.
Therefore, the government introduced comparative tests across the country.
In order for children to start learning earlier, the last year of kindergarten is free of charge. This is a model that has since been copied by other federal states.
Only future comparative studies will provide an answer as to whether the students&#39; performance improves permanently.
Based on the Pisa survey conducted in 2003, the proportion of students affected by the risk shrank from 29 to 20 percent.
However, the overall performance of the Saarland did not improve to the same extent as the other federal states.
Bavarians count better.
To the greatest annoyance of the people of the Saar region, knowledge of a foreign language is not taken into account during the Pisa assessment - otherwise, they would otherwise reap laurels in this area,
since the language of the neighboring countries is a compulsory subject in high schools - even if the people of the Saar region are not French.
