With &quot;The Hunt&quot; and &quot;Mörderischer Frieden&quot;, two films deal with the Balkan war again.
However, none of them are convincing.
The basic idea is either too much about action and shooting, or too sentimental.
Not even Richard Gere himself can help with this in &quot;The Hunt&quot;.
First, the good news: Although the two war criminals, Karadzic and Mladic, are still hiding in the Balkan mountains, the actor Richard Gere was found again right there, in the dark hinterland of the Bosnian war.
Lately, we have lost sight of the most beautiful man of the eighties, as the many good-guy-nothing roles he played in emotional films for women and the numerous press conferences on the subject of Buddhism took away our desire to even look at him.
And here, suddenly Richard Gere is the most compelling argument in favor of maybe watching &quot;The Hunt&quot; after all. movie.
